# This is a calculation of the ground-state of a Nitrogen molecule at the
# experimental equilibrium distance. The parameters of the calculation
# are not optimal (grid spacings, etc), but this way the test runs faster,
# and may be tagged as "short-run".
# The purpose is to test the calculation of the force on the atoms.

Input: 12-forces.01-N2_gs.inp

Match ; Total Energy ; grep -A 7 '^Energy:' static/info ; \s*Total\s*=\s*-19.9380
Match ; Force        ; grep -A 2 '^Forces on' static/info | tail -1 ; \s*-0.08653\d*
